Server Creation - Nodejs + Expree


Basic commands
---------------------

1) Creating package.json - npm init
2)Creating node modules - npm i express (to install express )
3)Install nodemon - npm install nodemon
4)Run -nodemon.index.js

 Basic steps
 --------------

 1) Creating a folder
 2) Create package.json file
 3) Install express
 4) Import express inside the index.js file
 5) Create an app using express
 6) set up ort number
 7) resolve HTTP request

8) HTTP Response code
  1xx - Information
  2xx - Successful
  3xx - Redirection
  4xx - client error
  5xx - Server error

9) JWT token
  Install JWT token - npm i jsonwebtoken
  To generate token - sign()

10) Middleware
   It comes in the midde of the request and response cycle of nodejs execution process
    req,res,next

    i) Application specific middleware - for entire application
    ii) ROuter specific middleware - for token verification - verify()

11) Database Integration
   i) install mongoose - npm i mongoose

13)Asynchronous function resolving - promise
  i)Resolve state - .then()
  ii)Reject state - catch()

14)CORS - Cross Origin Resource Sharing
   install cors - npm i cors

   port 4200 (angular) --------requests----------------> 3000(node)(receives)
   
15)Asynchronous call - RxJs - (Reactive Extention for JavaScript)

   JS - promise
   TypeScript - RxJs(it's a library)

     1)Obsrvable
         a)resolved - subscribe()
         b)reject - catch()
